OL,3,C'Do not ever use my music': Ariana
OL,4,CGrande tells White House after ICE post
OL,6,FBy Producer James Hockaday
OL,8,FAriana Grande has told the White House
OL,9,Fnot to use her music, after her song
OL,10,F'Bye' was featured in a TikTok video
OL,11,Fabout US Immigration and Customs
OL,12,FEnforcement (ICE) deportations.
OL,14,FThe 'We Can't Be Friends' singer has
OL,15,Fnow joined a long list of artists who
OL,16,Fhave taken issue with the US
OL,17,Fgovernment, or politicians, using
OL,18,Ftheir music for their own political
OL,19,Fagendas.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781287881
OL,3,C'Do not ever use my music': Ariana
OL,4,CGrande tells White House after ICE post
OL,6,FThe TikTok video shows a montage of
OL,7,FICE agents detaining people and
OL,8,Fleading them away with their hands
OL,9,Fcuffed behind their backs, with the
OL,10,Fcaption: "Bye-bye. President Trump has
OL,11,Fdelivered the most secure border in
OL,12,Fhistory."
OL,14,FResponding directly in the comments
OL,15,Fsection, the Los Angeles Times reports
OL,16,FGrande as writing: "Please do not ever
OL,17,Fuse my music in relation to this
OL,18,Fbarbaric, inhumane, heinous nonsense.
OL,19,FF` ice."
OL,26,@xD@TOU{D@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
