OL,3,C'Do not ever use my music': Ariana
OL,4,CGrande tells White House after ICE post
OL,6,FGrande joins a long list of artists
OL,7,Fwho have asked the US government and
OL,8,Fpolitical parties to stop using their
OL,9,Fwork. Here are some big names who have
OL,10,Frebuked politicians for using their
OL,11,Fmusic without permission:
OL,13,FSabrina Carpenter
OL,15,FSabrina Carpenter lashed out at the
OL,16,FWhite House over a now-deleted video
OL,17,Fposted on X in December showing
OL,18,Fimmigration raids to the soundtrack of
OL,19,Fher song, 'Juno'.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781287881
OL,3,C'Do not ever use my music': Ariana
OL,4,CGrande tells White House after ICE post
OL,6,F"This video is evil and disgusting. Do
OL,7,Fnot ever involve me or my music to
OL,8,Fbenefit your inhumane agenda," the
OL,9,F'Espresso' singer said.
OL,11,FSinger-songwriter SZA suggested the
OL,12,FWhite House's strategy is to "rage
OL,13,Fbait" artists for "free promo" after
OL,14,Fher song, 'Big Boys', was used in a
OL,15,Fmigrant deportation video.
OL,17,F"WE HEARD IT'S CUFFING SZN," the White
OL,18,FHouse wrote on its X post in December.
OL,19,F"Bad news for criminal illegal aliens.
OL,20,FGreat news for America."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
